    <description>
Command-line tool for controlling USB cameras on Windows using DirectShow UVC interface.

Features:
- List connected USB cameras
- get/set Camera and Video properties (exposure, focus, brightness, contrast, saturation)
- PTZ (Pan/Tilt/Zoom) operations
- No special drivers required, works with standard UVC cameras out of the box

Usage:
  duvc-cli list-devices
  duvc-cli get-property --device-id 0 --property zoom
  duvc-cli set-property --device-id 0 --property zoom --value 50

Requirements:
- Windows 7 or later
- USB camera with UVC support (supported by almost all usb cameras)
